", "APPROVAL OF MINUTES FROM PREVIOUS MEETINGS", "1. Minutes of the Decision Meeting from May 11, 2021. Minutes have been circulated to Action Item:", "the Commissioners for review and are ready for consideration.", "CONSENT AGENDA", "2. John R. Hammond Jr.\u2019s May 13, 2021, Decision Memorandum re: In the Matter of the Action Item:", "Petition of Commission Staff to Update Inputs to the Colstrip Method; Case Nos. AVU-E-21-05 and IPC-", "E-21-14.", "Matt Hunter\u2019s May 3. 13, 2021, Decision Memorandum re: In the Matter of Idaho Power Action Item:", "Application for a Determination Company\u2019s Acknowledging its North Valmy Power Plant Exit Date;", "Case No. IPC-E-21-12.", "4. Daniel Klein\u2019s May 14, 2021, Decision Memorandum re: The 2020 Broadband Action Item:", "Equipment Tax Credit Application for Direct Communications Rockland, Inc.; Case No. DCM-T-21-01.", "5. Curtis Thaden\u2019s May 14, 2021, Decision Memorandum re: Idaho Power Tariff Advice Action Item:", "No. 21-01; Revision to Idaho Power\u2019s Electric Service Schedule 95 Franchise Agreement with the City of", "Hagerman.", "MATTERS IN PROGRESS", "6. Dayn Hardie\u2019s May 14, 2021, Decision Memorandum re: In the Matter of Rocky Action Item:", "Mountain Power\u2019s Application for Approval or Rejection of the Power Purchase Agreement with Chester", "Diversion Project; Case No. PAC-E-21-06.", "RULEMAKING", "None.", "FULLY SUBMITTED MATTERS", "7. Deliberation re: In the Matter of Commnet Wireless, LLC\u2019s Application for Designation as an", "Eligible Telecommunications Carrier in the State of Idaho for Purposes of Receiving Rural Digital", "Opportunity Fund Support; Case No. CWL-T-21-01 [John R. Hammond, Jr., Attorney].", "8. Deliberation re: In the Matter of Idaho Power Company\u2019s Application for an Accounting Order", "Authorizing the Deferral of Incremental Wildfire Mitigation and Insurance Costs; Case No. IPC-E-21-02", "[Dayn Hardie, Attorney].", "In the Matter of Idaho Power\u2019s App